      <odd id="aspace_0aa4f0ceab9f2cd0ec4c596aa6fea1be">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Yale Record Group 46-A (YRG 46-A), Records and materials broadly documenting Yale buildings, facilities, and grounds.</p>  
      </odd>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_9d7ddbbc4e8b5f04323043f850628be8">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
         <p>Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_342dcf3bd941b63fc2e9402f80f4e11d">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Yale University Buildings and Grounds Negatives and Photographs (RU 705). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_4372262da56e8f760edf08cea638e119">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of photographs and negatives of maps, plans, and pictures of Yale buildings depicted between 1748-1919. The negatives are not dated.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_6b66b82e67d0a830da288ee1c24db2ef">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by subject.</p>  
      </arrangement>
